BERLIN, April 20. -- The Dukes of Mecklenburg-Schwerin are much in the public eye nowadays. The ruling Grand Duke, Frederick Francis IV., is about to grant to his country a Constitution. Duke John Albert is to be made Regent of Brunswick. Everybody remembers the gallant deed of Duke Henry, who as Prince of the Netherlands did rescue work off the Hook of Holland two or three months ago. View Full Article in Timesmachine Â»
